nerate one single body<br />of the function, and particularly one that is _different_ from the<br />inlining case (ie for inlining you want to do the simple thing, for<br />out-of-line you do something fancier).<br /><br />But that isn't the case here, so this looks like a workaround for<br />something else. But this code does end up using preprocessor<br />concatenation etc, so I might be missing some case.<br /><br />             Linus<br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
